==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sapan wood
<hw>Sa*pan" wood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Malay
<ets>sapang</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A dyewood yielded by
<spn>Caesalpinia Sappan</spn>, a thorny leguminous tree of Southern Asia
and the neighboring islands. It is the original Brazil wood.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>sappan wood</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sapful</ent>⟦br⟧
